One flood alert was in place for rivers in the Ewenny and Vale of Glamorgan west areas on Monday morning.
There are restrictions in place on the Severn Bridge M48 crossing due to strong winds but it remains open.
Stena Lines cancelled its 14:30 GMT sailing from Fishguard in Pembrokeshire to Rosslare, Ireland, due to adverse weather.
